r/en/africa/covid-19-gambia-senegal-to-close-border-for-21-days/1776298 |accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ghana}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Ghana will ban anyone that has been to a country with more than 200 cases in the previous 14 days, unless they are an official resident or a Ghanaian national. Citizens and resident-permit holders will be required to self-isolate for 14 days on arrival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-15/ghana-closes-borders-for-arrivals-from-coronavirus-hit-countries |title=Africa Virus News, Ghana Latest: Borders Close For Some |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2020-03-15 |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Kenya}}: Effective March 17, 2020 Kenya halted the entry of foreigners from countries that have confirmed coronavirus cases. Only Kenyan citizens, and any foreigners with valid residence permits will be allowed to come in provided they proceed on self-quarantine or to a government designated quarantine facility.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-15/kenya-restricts-foreign-travel-suspends-school-on-coronavirus |title=Africa, Kenya, Coronavirus News: Travel, Schools Hit by Virus Ban |publisher=Bloomberg |date=2020-03-15 |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Madagascar}}: All flights to Madagascar are suspended until 20 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3609 | title=Madagascar - restriction update 01.04.2020 12:24 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Mauritius}}: Passengers are not allowed to transit or enter Mauritius.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3615 | title=Mauritius - restriction update 01.04.2020 21:44 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Morocco}}: On March 15, 2020 Morocco suspended all international passenger flights to and from the country.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kirsten Donovan|date=March 15, 2020|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-cor