 place to disallow travellers to Bermuda unless the person is a Bermuda resident, a crew member, or a person with the written permission of the Quarantine Authority of Bermuda to enter.<ref>{{Citation | url = https://www.gov.bm/coronavirus | title = Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) - Information for Travellers | date = 10 March 2020 | publisher = Govenment of Bermuda | accessdate = 2020-03-20}}</ref> Flights to Bermuda are suspended until 1 May 2020.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3740 | title=Bermuda - restriction update 02.04.2020 20:50 UTC: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Bolivia}}: Effective March 20, Borders closed to foreigners and international flights cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lostiempos.com/actualidad/pais/20200317/bolivia-cierra-fronteras-suspende-vuelos-limita-transporte-terrestre|title=Bolivia cierra fronteras, suspende vuelos y limita el transporte terrestre por el coronavirus|date=March 17, 2020|website=Los Tiempos}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Brazil}}: Effective March 30, 2020, passengers are not allowed to enter Brazil except specific categories of passengers.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://restrictions.info/news/detail/3536 | title=Brazil - restrictions update 30.03.2020: COVID-19 Travel Restrictions Database}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Canada}}: Borders are closed to all travellers who are not citizens, permanent residents or U.S. citizens. Exceptions are placed for diplomats, crew and immediate family members of citizens with clearing a basic health assessment by air operators.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/cbsa-border-airports-screening-trudeau-covid19-coronavirus-1.5498866 |title = Canada to bar entry to travellers who are not citizens, permanent residents or Americans | work = CBC News | date = March 16, 2020 | accessdate = March 20, 2020}}</ref> The U.S. and Canada later agreed to close the [[Canada\u2013United States border]] to non-essential traffic.<ref>{{Cite news | url = https