{"title_page": "Keith Frazier (musician)", "text_new": "'''Keith Frazier''' is one of the founding members of [[Rebirth Brass Band]].  In the band, Frazier plays the [[bass drum]] with a [[cymbal]] mounted on top.  He plays the drum with one hand and the cymbal with the other, using a flathead screwdriver.<ref>''Fly Fishing with Darth Vader'' by Matt Labash, Simon and Schuster, Feb 9, 2010</ref>\n\nKeith Frazier and his brother, Phillip Frazier (the group's [[sousaphone]]/[[tuba]] player), formed [[Rebirth Brass Band]], along with other band members they met (including renowned trumpeter, [[Kermit Ruffins]]) with students at Joseph S. Clark Sr. High School in [[New Orleans]]. In Joseph S. Clark's marching and concert bands, Frazier played several brass instruments and was section leader of the baritones.\n\n[[Rebirth Brass Band]],  was discovered at the 1982 New Orleans Jazz & Heritage Festival and recorded its first studio album in 1984.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Rebirth Brass Band]]\n* [[Treme (TV series)|HBO's ''Treme'' TV Series]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://greenville.metromix.com/music/article/q-and-a-keith/2085705/content/ Keith Frazier Interview - Metromix] article by Matt Wake\n*[http://www.rebirthbrassband.com/ Rebirth Brass Band website]\n*[http://www.pastemagazine.com/action/article/7499/feature/music/still_bustin_loose_rebirth_brass_band_turns_25 Rebirth Turns 25], [[Paste Magazine]] article by Caroline Goyette\n\n{{Rebirth Brass Band}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Frazier, Keith}}\n<!--- Categories --->\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from New Orleans]]\n[[Category:American percussionists]]\n[[Category:Rebirth Brass Band members]]\n", "text_old": "'''Keith Frazier''' is one of the founding members of [[Rebirth Brass Band]].  In the band, Frazier plays the [[bass drum]] with a [[cymbal]] mounted on top.  He plays the drum with one hand and the cymbal with the other, using a flathead screwdriver. <ref>''Fly Fishing with Darth Vader'' by Matt Labash, Simon and Schuster, Feb 9, 2010]</ref> \n\nKeith Frazier and his brother, Phillip Frazier (the group's [[sousaphone]]/[[tuba]] player), formed [[Rebirth Brass Band]], along with other band members they met (including renowned trumpeter, [[Kermit Ruffins]]) with students at Joseph S. Clark Sr. High School in [[New Orleans]]. In Joseph S. Clark's marching and concert bands, Frazier played several brass instruments and was section leader of the baritones.\n\n[[Rebirth Brass Band]],  was discovered at the 1982 New Orleans Jazz & Heritage Festival and recorded its first studio album in 1984.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Rebirth Brass Band]]\n* [[Treme (TV series)|HBO's ''Treme'' TV Series]]\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://greenville.metromix.com/music/article/q-and-a-keith/2085705/content/ Keith Frazier Interview - Metromix] article by Matt Wake\n*[http://www.rebirthbrassband.com/ Rebirth Brass Band website]\n*[http://www.pastemagazine.com/action/article/7499/feature/music/still_bustin_loose_rebirth_brass_band_turns_25 Rebirth Turns 25], [[Paste Magazine]] article by Caroline Goyette\n\n\n{{Rebirth Brass Band}}\n<!--- Categories --->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Frazier, Keith}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from New Orleans]]\n[[Category:American percussionists]]\n[[Category:Rebirth Brass Band members]]\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "unbalanced brackets", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keith_Frazier_(musician)"}
{"title_page": "I'm Ready (Sam Smith and Demi Lovato song)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|2020 single by Sam Smith and Demi Lovato}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = I'm Ready\n| cover         = Sam Smith - I'm Ready.png\n| alt           = \n| border        = yes\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[Sam Smith]] and [[Demi Lovato]]\n| album         = '[[Upcoming Sam Smith album|Untitled]]'\n| released      = {{Start date|2020|04|16|df=y}}\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre         = <!--do not add unsourced genres; genres sourced in composition section-->\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length        = {{Duration|m=3|s=20}}\n| label         = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| writer        =\n* [[Sam Smith]]\n* [[Demi Lovato]]\n* [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]]\n* [[Savan Kotecha]]\n* [[Peter Svensson]]\n| producer      = Ilya\n| chronology    = [[Sam Smith]] singles\n| prev_title    = [[To Die For (Sam Smith song)|To Die For]]\n| prev_year     = 2020\n| next_title    = \n| next_year     = \n| misc          = {{Extra chronology\n | artist       = [[Demi Lovato]]\n | type         = single\n | prev_title   = [[I Love Me (song)|I Love Me]]\n | prev_year    = 2020\n | title        = I'm Ready\n | year         = 2020\n | next_title   = \n | next_year    =\n }}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|glD1M418bC0|\"I'm Ready\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''I'm Ready'''\" is a song by English singer [[Sam Smith]] and American singer [[Demi Lovato]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Peters |first=Mitchell |title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Announce New Collaboration |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9356689/sam-smith-demi-lovato-tease-upcoming-song-collaboration |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |location=United States |date=12 April 2020}}</ref> released through [[Capitol Records]] on 16 April 2020. Smith and Lovato co-wrote \"I'm Ready\" with [[Savan Kotecha]], [[Peter Svensson]], and the song's producer, [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ascap.com/repertory#ace/search/workID/907295380|title=ACE Repertory|website=www.ascap.com|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background and release ==\nIn an interview, Smith shared that they \"grew up listening to\" and \"singing\" Lovato's music, calling her an \"incredible talent\" and \"everything she stands for as a human being\". Thus, they revealed that they had been \"training\" for the moment to collaborate with Lovato for a long time. Smith also said that they had already been in contact as a friend to Lovato for years, and Lovato was invited to the studio by their mutual songwriter [[Savan Kotecha]], which is what led to the collaboration happening.<ref>{{cite web |last=Croezen |first=Alyssa |title=Sam Smith Discusses New Single 'I'm Ready' featuring Demi Lovato: 'I've Been Training for This Moment for a Long Time' |url=https://etcanada.com/news/624058/sam-smith-discusses-new-single-im-ready-featuring-demi-lovato-ive-been-training-for-this-moment-for-a-long-time/ |website=[[ET Canada]] |publisher=[[Corus Entertainment]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200413165352/https://etcanada.com/news/624058/sam-smith-discusses-new-single-im-ready-featuring-demi-lovato-ive-been-training-for-this-moment-for-a-long-time/ |archivedate=13 April 2020 |location=Canada |date=13 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April, Smith shared a polaroid of Smith and Lovato in the studio, captioned with \"S + D 4 EVA\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7909200/sam-smith-demi-lovato-tease-their-collaboration-on-social-media|title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Tease Their Collaboration on Social Media|date=9 April 2020|website=Idolator|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> Smith also teased the duet on social media, tweeting \"YOU READY\" and tagging Lovato with a GIF that displays Smith and Lovato's initials; Lovato responded with \"I'M READY\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9356689/sam-smith-demi-lovato-tease-upcoming-song-collaboration|title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Announce New Collaboration|date=13 April 2020|website=Billboard|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> On 13 April, Smith and Lovato announced the title of the duet and its release date.<ref name=\"umusic 1\">{{cite web |title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato \u2013 I'm Ready |url=https://umusic.digital/imready/ |website=[[Universal Music Group]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=[[Capitol Music Group]] |title=Sam Smith and Demi Lovato announce new single |url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/CapitolMusicGroup/view/209098/ |website=[[Pressparty]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=en |date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nDescribed by Smith as \"2020 [[ABBA]]\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/9359669/sam-smith-demi-lovato-collab-interview |title=Sam Smith Shares More Details of Their '2020 Abba' Collab With Demi Lovato |date=16 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |last=Daw |first=Stephen}}</ref> \"I'm Ready\" is a [[pop music|pop]]<ref name = \"People\">{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/demi-lovato-sam-smith-im-ready-music-video/ |title=Demi Lovato and Sam Smith Debut 'Musical Theater'-Inspired Duet 'I'm Ready' \u2014 Complete with Drag Queens! |last=Aderoju |first=Darlene |date=16 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref> song with elements of [[disco]].<ref name = \"Teen Vogue\">{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/sam-smith-demi-lovato-im-ready-music-video |title=Sam Smith, Demi Lovato Created a Literal Drag Race in \"I'm Ready\" Music Video |last=Delgado |first=Sara |date=17 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Teen Vogue]]}}</ref> The song features an \"edgy\" production, gospel choirs and a \"[[bass guitar|bass]]-y\" chorus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/sam-smith-demi-lovato-duet-song-im-ready-1234583802/ |title=As Duet With Demi Lovato Debuts, It\u2019s a Party of One for Sam Smith: \u2018Cheers, Darlings!\u2019 |last=Herman |first=James Patrick |date=17 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9360112/sam-smith-demi-lovato-im-ready-video |title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Conquer the Olympics in Powerful 'I'm Ready' Video |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |date=16 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> Lyrically, it is a \"feel-good love song\"<ref name = \"Teen Vogue\"/> about \"having the bravery to be vulnerable and accepting of love\".<ref name = \"People\"/>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was released on 17 April 2020. It was directed by Jora Frantzis, mostly known by her work on the 2019 music video of \"[[Money (Cardi B song)|Money]]\", by [[Cardi B]].\nThe music video opens on Smith circling a man on the wrestling mat, as they sing about \"waiting patiently for a beautiful lover\" and vowing to \"take that risk tonight\" with someone new. As the instrumental approaches the bridge of the song, Smith lines up for a 100-meter sprint \u2014 they and their equally glam competitors dash off in sky-high stilettos, voluminous skirts, and impeccably applied makeup. These competitors include [[Valentina (drag queen)|Valentina]], Gigi Goode, Dee TrannyBear, Alok Vaid-Menon, [[Shea Diamond]] and Jeffrey C. Williams.\nThe second verse of the song is taken over by Lovato; she holds court on a tall diving board, and singing as swimmers dive into the pool around her. She and Smith eventually come together for the song's big climax, which takes them to a gymnast-filled medal ceremony.\nPrior to the video's premiere, Smith and Lovato hopped on a video chat to reminisce about writing the song together.<ref>{{cite web |author=Madeline Roth |title=Sam Smith and Demi Lovato are an olympic dream team in \"I'm Ready\" video |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3163246/sam-smith-demi-lovato-im-ready-video/ |website=[[MTV]] |accessdate=17 April 2020 |language=en |date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/136989881/credits |title=Credits / I'm Ready / Sam Smith |website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]] |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* [[Sam Smith]] \u2013 [[songwriter|songwriting]], [[singing|vocals]], [[backing vocalist|backing vocals]]\n* [[Demi Lovato]] \u2013 songwriting, vocals\n* [[Ilya]] \u2013 [[record producer|production]], songwriting, [[bass guitar|bass]], [[drum|drums]], [[guitar]], [[musical keyboard|keyboards]], [[percussion instrument|percussion]], [[programming (music)|programming]]\n* [[Peter Svensson]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Savan Kotecha]] \u2013 songwriting\n* Wojtek Goral \u2013 [[alto saxophone]]\n* David Bukovinszky \u2013 [[cello]]\n* [[Carolina Liar|Johan Carlsson]] \u2013 [[piano]]\n* Mattias Bylund \u2013 [[String instrument|strings]], [[String section|string arrangement]]\n* Tomas Jonsson \u2013 [[tenor saxophone]]\n* Peter Noos Johansson \u2013 [[trombone]]\n* Janne Bjerger \u2013 [[trumpet]]\n* Magnus Johansson \u2013 trumpet\n* Mattias Johansson \u2013 [[violin]]\n* John Hanes \u2013 [[audio engineer|engineering]], [[Recording studio|studio personnel]]\n* Sam Holland \u2013 engineering, studio personnel\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]], studio personnel\n* Randy Merrill \u2013 [[mastering (audio)|mastering]], studio personnel\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Release history ==\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of releases showing region, date, format, record label and reference\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|R