ublisher=Radio Today Pty Ltd |accessdate=18 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419133812/https://themusicnetwork.com/charts/issues/1285/1285-singles-to-radio/ |archivedate=19 April 2020 |location=Australia |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Sam Smith}}\n{{Demi Lovato}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Sam Smith (singer) songs]]\n[[Category:Demi Lovato songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sam Smith (singer)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Demi Lovato]]\n\n{{2020s-single-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|2020 single by Sam Smith and Demi Lovato}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = I'm Ready\n| cover         = Sam Smith - I'm Ready.png\n| alt           = \n| border        = yes\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[Sam Smith]] and [[Demi Lovato]]\n| album         = '[[Upcoming Sam Smith album]]'\n| released      = {{Start date|2020|04|16|df=y}}\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre         = <!--do not add unsourced genres; genres sourced in composition section-->\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length        = {{Duration|m=3|s=20}}\n| label         = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| writer        =\n* [[Sam Smith]]\n* [[Demi Lovato]]\n* [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]]\n* [[Savan Kotecha]]\n* [[Peter Svensson]]\n| producer      = Ilya\n| chronology    = [[Sam Smith]] singles\n| prev_title    = [[To Die For (Sam Smith song)|To Die For]]\n| prev_year     = 2020\n| next_title    = \n| next_year     = \n| misc          = {{Extra chronology\n | artist       = [[Demi Lovato]]\n | type         = single\n | prev_title   = [[I Love Me (song)|I Love Me]]\n | prev_year    = 2020\n | title        = I'm Ready\n | year         = 2020\n | next_title   = \n | next_year    =\n }}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|glD1M418bC0|\"I'm Ready\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''I'm Ready'''\" is a song by English singer [[Sam Smith]] and American singer [[Demi Lovato]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Peters |first=Mitchell |title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Announce New Collaboration |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9356689/sam-smith-demi-lovato-tease-upcoming-song-collaboration |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |location=United States |date=12 April 2020}}</ref> released through [[Capitol Records]] on 16 April 2020. Smith and Lovato co-wrote \"I'm Ready\" with [[Savan Kotecha]], [[Peter Svensson]], and the song's producer, [[Ilya Salmanzadeh]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ascap.com/repertory#ace/search/workID/907295380|title=ACE Repertory|website=www.ascap.com|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background and release ==\nIn an interview, Smith shared that they \"grew up listening to\" and \"singing\" Lovato's music, calling her an \"incredible talent\" and \"everything she stands for as a human being\". Thus, they revealed that they had been \"training\" for the moment to collaborate with Lovato for a long time. Smith also said that they had already been in contact as a friend to Lovato for years, and Lovato was invited to the studio by their mutual songwriter [[Savan Kotecha]], which is what led to the collaboration happening.<ref>{{cite web |last=Croezen |first=Alyssa |title=Sam Smith Discusses New Single 'I'm Ready' featuring Demi Lovato: 'I've Been Training for This Moment for a Long Time' |url=https://etcanada.com/news/624058/sam-smith-discusses-new-single-im-ready-featuring-demi-lovato-ive-been-training-for-this-moment-for-a-long-time/ |website=[[ET Canada]] |publisher=[[Corus Entertainment]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200413165352/https://etcanada.com/news/624058/sam-smith-discusses-new-single-im-ready-featuring-demi-lovato-ive-been-training-for-this-moment-for-a-long-time/ |archivedate=13 April 2020 |location=Canada |date=13 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April, Smith shared a polaroid of Smith and Lovato in the studio, captioned with \"S + D 4 EVA\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7909200/sam-smith-demi-lovato-tease-their-collaboration-on-social-media|title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Tease Their Collaboration on Social Media|date=9 April 2020|website=Idolator|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> Smith also teased the duet on social media, tweeting \"YOU READY\" and tagging Lovato with a GIF that displays Smith and Lovato's initials; Lovato responded with \"I'M READY\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9356689/sam-smith-demi-lovato-tease-upcoming-song-collaboration|title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Announce New Collaboration|date=13 April 2020|website=Billboard|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> On 13 April, Smith and Lovato announced the title of the duet and its release date.<ref name=\"umusic 1\">{{cite web |title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato \u2013 I'm Ready |url=https://umusic.digital/imready/ |website=[[Universal Music Group]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=[[Capitol Music Group]] |title=Sam Smith and Demi Lovato announce new single |url=https://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/CapitolMusicGroup/view/209098/ |website=[[Pressparty]] |accessdate=13 April 2020 |language=en |date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\nDescribed by Smith as \"2020 [[ABBA]]\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/9359669/sam-smith-demi-lovato-collab-interview |title=Sam Smith Shares More Details of Their '2020 Abba' Collab With Demi Lovato |date=16 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |last=Daw |first=Stephen}}</ref> \"I'm Ready\" is a [[pop music|pop]]<ref name = \"People\">{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/demi-lovato-sam-smith-im-ready-music-video/ |title=Demi Lovato and Sam Smith Debut 'Musical Theater'-Inspired Duet 'I'm Ready' \u2014 Complete with Drag Queens! |last=Aderoju |first=Darlene |date=16 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref> song with elements of [[disco]].<ref name = \"Teen Vogue\">{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/sam-smith-demi-lovato-im-ready-music-video |title=Sam Smith, Demi Lovato Created a Literal Drag Race in \"I'm Ready\" Music Video |last=Delgado |first=Sara |date=17 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Teen Vogue]]}}</ref> The song features an \"edgy\" production, gospel choirs and a \"[[bass guitar|bass]]-y\" chorus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/sam-smith-demi-lovato-duet-song-im-ready-1234583802/ |title=As Duet With Demi Lovato Debuts, It\u2019s a Party of One for Sam Smith: \u2018Cheers, Darlings!\u2019 |last=Herman |first=James Patrick |date=17 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9360112/sam-smith-demi-lovato-im-ready-video |title=Sam Smith & Demi Lovato Conquer the Olympics in Powerful 'I'm Ready' Video |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |date=16 April 2020 |accessdate=18 April 2020 |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> Lyrically, it is a \"feel-good love song\"<ref name = \"Teen Vogue\"/> about \"having the bravery to be vulnerable and accepting of love\".<ref name = \"People\"/>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was released on 17 April 2020. It was directed by Jora Frantzis, mostly known by her work on the 2019 music video of \"[[Money (Cardi B song)|Money]]\", by [[Cardi B]].\nThe music video opens on Smith circling a man on the wrestling mat, as they sing about \"waiting patiently for a beautiful lover\" and vowing to \"take that risk tonight\" with someone new. As the instrumental approaches the bridge of the song, Smith lines up for a 100-meter sprint \u2014 they and their equally glam competitors dash off in sky-high stilettos, voluminous skirts, and impeccably applied makeup. These competitors include [[Valentina (drag queen)|Valentina]], Gigi Goode, Dee TrannyBear, Alok Vaid-Menon, [[Shea Diamond]] and Jeffrey C. Williams.\nThe second verse of the song is taken over by Lovato; she holds court on a tall diving board, and singing as swimmers dive into the pool around her. She and Smith eventually come together for the song's big climax, which takes them to a gymnast-filled medal ceremony.\nPrior to the video's premiere, Smith and Lovato hopped on a video chat to reminisce about writing the song together.<ref>{{cite web |author=Madeline Roth |title=Sam Smith and Demi Lovato are an olympic dream team in \"I'm Ready\" video |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3163246/sam-smith-demi-lovato-im-ready-video/ |website=[[MTV]] |accessdate=17 April 2020 |language=en |date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/136989881/credits |title=Credits / I'm Ready / Sam Smith |website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]] |accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n* [[Sam Smith]] \u2013 [[songwriter|songwriting]], [[singing|vocals]], [[backing vocalist|backing vocals]]\n* [[Demi Lovato]] \u2013 songwriting, vocals\n* [[Ilya]] \u2013 [[record producer|production]], songwriting, [[bass guitar|bass]], [[drum|drums]], [[guitar]], [[musical keyboard|keyboards]], [[percussion instrument|percussion]], [[programming (music)|programming]]\n* [[Peter Svensson]] \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Savan Kotecha]] \u2013 songwriting\n* Wojtek Goral \u2013 [[alto saxophone]]\n* David Bukovinszky \u2013 [[cello]]\n* [[Carolina Liar|Johan Carlsson]] \u2013 [[piano]]\n* Mattias Bylund \u2013 [[String instrument|strings]], [[String section|string arrangement]]\n* Tomas Jonsson \u2013 [[tenor saxophone]]\n* Peter Noos Johansson \u2013 [[trombone]]\n* Janne Bjerger \u2013 [[trumpet]]\n* Magnus Johansson \u2013 trumpet\n* Mattias Johansson \u2013 [[violin]]\n* John Hanes \u2013 [[audio engineer|engineering]], [[Recording studio|studio personnel]]\n* Sam Holland \u2013 engineering, studio personnel\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]], studio personnel\n* Randy Merrill \u2013 [[mastering (audio)|mastering]], studio personnel\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Release history ==\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of releases showing region, date, format, record label and reference\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| 16 April 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=I'm Ready \u2013 Single by Sam Smith & Demi Lovato |url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/im-ready-single/1506964419 |website=[[Apple Music]] |accessdate=16 April 2020 |location=United States}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Italy\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 17 April 2020\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| [[List of Universal Music Group labels#Other Universal Music Group national companies|Universal]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://radiodate.it/radio-date/sam-smith-demi-lovato-i-m-ready-200436-17-04-2020-radiodate/|title=Sam Smith I'm Ready|website=radiodate.it|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| United Kingdom\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Capitol\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/3tqPdBWF9yMbTrfjWvfKV8t/radio-1-playlist|title=BBC - Radio 1 Playlist|website=[[BBC]]|accessdate=17 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417124841/https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/3tqPdBWF9yMbTrfjWvfKV8t/radio-1-playlist|archive-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Adult contemporary radio]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/2qNJsnjYFvbLrK9CZ0CfYfM/radio-2-new-music-playlist|title=BBC - Radio 2 Playlist|website=[[BBC]]|accessdate=17 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417125017/https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/2qNJsnjYFvbLrK9CZ0CfYfM/radio-2-new-music-playlist|archive-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia\t\n| Contemporary hit radio\t\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=Singles to Radio: Issue 1285 |url=https://themusicnetwork.com/charts/issues/1285/1285-singles-to-radio/ |website=[[The Music Network]] |publisher=Radio Today Pty Ltd |accessdate=18 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419133812/https://themusicnetwork.com/charts/issues/1285/1285-singles-to-radio/ |archivedate=19 April 2020 |location=Australia |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Sam Smith}}\n{{Demi Lovato}}\n\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:Sam Smith (singer) songs]]\n[[Category:Demi Lovato songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sam Smith (singer)]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Demi Lovato]]\n\n{{2020s-single-stub}}\n", "name_user": "LOVI33", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I%27m_Ready_(Sam_Smith_and_Demi_Lovato_song)"}
{"title_page": "Government Saadat College", "text_new": "{{Primary sources|date=November 2008}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name           = Govt. Saadat College, Tangail\n|image          =\n|motto          = \"\u0986\u09b2\u09cb\u0995\u09bf\u09a4 \u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09c1\u09b7 \u09b8\u09c3\u09b7\u09cd\u099f\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09be\"(''To create enlightened human being'')<ref name=\"GSC\">{{cite news |last=Annual college magazine |title=Suborno joyonti soronika |work= |publisher=Saadat College |year=1977 |language=bn}}</ref>\n|established    = 1926\n|type           = [[Public university|Public]]\n|staff          =\n|faculty        = 120<ref name=\"GSC\"/>\n|chancellor     = Rezaul Karim\n|students       = 20000<ref name=\"GSC\"/>\n|city           = [[Tangail]]\n|state          =\n|country        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| coor = {{coord|24.220|89.976|type:edu_region:BD|display=inline,title}}\n|campus         = [[Karatia]], 38 acres (0.15km<sup>''2''</sup>)<ref name=\"GSC\"/>\n|nickname       =\n|address        =\n}}\n'''Government Saadat College''' ({{lang-bn|\u09b8\u09b0\u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 \u09b8\u09be'\u09a6\u09a4 \u0995\u09b2\u09c7\u099c}}) is a public college in [[Karatia, Tangail]], [[Bangladesh]]. It is often referred to as '''Karatia College'''.It was established in July 1926. The college is located at Karatia near the [[Dhaka]]-[[Tangail]] highway and about 7 kilometres from the Tangail district. First Principal of the college [[Ibrahim Khan (writer)|Ibrahim Khan]] who is the Founder and Principal of Bhuapur College at Bhuapur, Tangail. Later named Ibrahim Khan Govt. College.\n\n==History==\n[[Image:GSC building.jpg|thumb|270px|right|Main administrative building]]\n[[Image:Entrance GSC.jpg|thumb|100px|left|Entrance to Saadat College]]\nSadat college is the first college in Bangladesh established by a Muslim Zamindar.<ref name=\"GSC\"/> It was founded by [[Wazed Ali Khan Panni]], a [[zamindar]] and [[educationalist]] of Tangail. He named it after his grandfather [[Saadat Ali Khan Panni]]. The founder member of Saadat college was Principal Ibrahim Khan. He was the first chief executive of the college. He worked in college till 1947.<ref>{{cite book |last=Sheren |first=Syeda Momtaz |year=2012 |chapter=Sadat College |chapter-url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Sadat_College |editor1-last=Islam |editor1-first=Sirajul |editor1-link=Sirajul Islam |editor2-last=Jamal |editor2-first=Ahmed A. |title=Banglapedia: National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh |edition=Second |publisher=[[Asiatic Society of Bangladesh]]}}</ref> The college was upgraded as a [[academic degree|degree]] college in 1938.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}} In Saadat college, the [[Honors course|Honours]] course was commenced in 1966 and the [[Master degree|Masters]] course was commenced in 1974.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}} The [[Government of Bangladesh]] promulgated the Saadat college as a national university college on July 7, 1979. It has Honours programme in 16 subjects and Masters programme in 10 subjects. The college is recognised as a postgraduate college.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\nThe college played a vital role in the liberation war of Bangladesh. There are so many reputed student of this college made influence in Bangladesh's socio-political circumstances.\n\n==Faculties and departments==\nSaadat college comprises following four faculties:\n;Faculty of Arts ([[Bachelor degree|B.A]])\n* Department of [[English language|English]]\n* Department of [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n* Department of [[History]]\n* Department of [[Philosophy]]\n* Department of [[Islamic history]] and [[Islamic culture|culture]]\n* Department of [[Islamic studies|Islamic study]]\n;Faculty of Science ([[Bachelor degree|B.SC]])\n* Department of [[Physics]]\n* Department of [[Chemistry]]\n* Department of [[Math]]\n* Department of [[Zoology]]\n* Department of [[Botany]]\n;Faculty of Social Science ([[Bachelor degree|B.S.S]])\n* Department of [[Economics]]\n* Department of [[Social welfare]]\n* Department of [[Political science]]\n;Faculty of Commerce ([[Bachelor degree|B.B.A.]])\n* Department of [[Accounting]]\n* Department of [[Management]]\n* Department of [[Marketing]]\n* Department of [[Banking]]  & [[Finance]]\n\nThe college offers [[Master degree]] in English, Zoology, Chemistry, Mathematicsa\n\n==Facilities==\n[[Image:GSC library.jpg|thumb|210px|left|Central Library]]\nThe main building of this college is surrounded within {{convert|27|acre|m2}} of area. Inside the campus area there are one college auditorium, two students common room, one central library, one sports office, one B.N.CC office room, one [[Rover Scout|Rover scouts]] office, one Mosque and one canteen available for students. There are 5 laboratories available for science faculty - (I) Physics (ii) Chemistry (iii) Math (iv) Zoology and (v) Botany. The college also has 16 seminar rooms.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\nThe college library has 200 rare medieval [[manuscripts]], including some other manuscripts written by [[Shahnama]].<ref name=\"GSC\"/> Since its inception, the college has been providing [[lodging|lodging facilities]] for its students.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n==Halls of residence==\n[[Image:Panni hall.jpg|thumb|210px|right|Wazed Ali Khan Panni Hall]]\n[[Image:Chhatrinibas.jpg|thumb|210px|right|Chhatrinibas Hall]]\nThere are 6 residential halls to provide housing for Saadat college students. 4 for males and 2 for females.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}} The halls for male students are:\n* Wazed Ali Khan Panni Hall\n* Ebrahim Khan Hall\n* Somman Hall\n* Uttara Hall\nAnd the halls for female students are:\n* Fazilatunnesa Hall\n* Chhatrinibas Hall\n\n==Alumni==\nThis is a partial list of notable alumni of Government Saadat College. Entries on this list should either have an accompanying existing article link which verifies they are an alumnus, or reliable sources as footnotes against the name.\n* [[Selim Al Din]] (dramatist)\n* [[Shajahan Siraj]] (ex-minister)\n* [[P. C. Sorcar]] (magician)\n* [[Bonde Ali Mia]] (poet)\n* [[Shamsul Haque (Mymensingh politician)|Shamsul Haque]] (First Secretary of Awami Muslim League)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Karatia, Tangail]]\n\n==References==\n{{commons|Government Saadat College}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.facebook.com/saadatcollege Government Saadat College at Facebook]\n\n{{Public Colleges under National University in Bangladesh}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1926]]\n[[Category:1926 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Education in Tangail]]\n", "text_old": "{{Primary sources|date=November 2008}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name           = Govt. Saadat College, Tangail\n|image          =\n|motto          = \"\u0986\u09b2\u09cb\u0995\u09bf\u09a4 \u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09c1\u09b7 \u09b8\u09c3\u09b7\u09cd\u099f\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09be\"(''To create enlightened human being'')<ref name=\"GSC\">{{cite news |last=Annual college magazine |title=Suborno joyonti soronika |work= |publisher=Saadat College |year=1977 |language=bn}}</ref>\n|established    = 1926\n|type           = [[Public university|Public]]\n|staff          =\n|faculty        = 120<ref name=\"GSC\"/>\n|chancellor     = Rezaul Karim\n|students       = 20000<ref name=\"GSC\"/>\n|city           = [[Tangail]]\n|state          =\n|country        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| coor = {{coord|24.220|89.976|type:edu_region:BD|display=inline,title}}\n|campus         = [[Karatia]], 38 acres (0.15km<sup>''2''</sup>)<ref name=\"GSC\"/>\n|nickname       =\n|address        =\n}}\n'''Government Saadat College''' ({{lang-bn|\u09b8\u09b0\u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 \u09b8\u09be'\u09a6\u09a4 \u0995\u09b2\u09c7\u099c}}) is a public college in [[Karatia, Tangail]], [[Bangladesh]]. It is often referred to as '''Karatia College'''.It was established in July 1926. The college is located at Karatia near the [[Dhaka]]-[[Tangail]] highway and about 7 kilometres from the Tangail district. First Principal of the college [[Ibrahim Khan (writer)|Ibrahim Khan]] who is the Founder and Principal of Bhuapur College at Bhuapur, Tangail. Later named Ibrahim Khan Govt. College.\n\n==History==\n[[Image:GSC building.jpg|thumb|270px|right|Main administrative building]]\n[[Image:Entrance GSC.jpg|thumb|100px|left|Entrance to Saadat College]]\nSadat college is the first college in Bangladesh established by a Muslim Zamindar.<ref name=\"GSC\"/> It was founded by [[Wazed Ali Khan Panni]], a [[zamindar]] and [[educationalist]] of Tangail. He named it after his grandfather [[Saadat Ali Khan Panni]]. The founder member of Saadat college was Principal Ibrahim Khan. He was the first chief executive of the college. He worked in college till 1947.<ref>{{cite book |last=Sheren |first=Syeda Momtaz |year=2012 |chapter=Sadat College |chapter-url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Sadat_College |editor1-last=Islam |editor1-first=Sirajul |editor1-link=Sirajul Islam |editor2-last=Jamal |editor2-first=Ahmed A. |title=Banglapedia: National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh |edition=Second |publisher=[[Asiatic Society of Bangladesh]]}}</ref> The college was upgraded as a [[academic degree|degree]] college in 1938.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}} In Saadat college, the [[Honors course|Honours]] course was commenced in 1966 and the [[Master degree|Masters]] course was commenced in 1974.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}} The [[Government of Bangladesh]] promulgated the Saadat college as a national university college on July 7, 1979. It has Honours programme in 16 subjects and Masters programme in 10 subjects. The college is recognised as a postgraduate college.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\nThe college played a vital role in the liberation war of Bangladesh. There are so many reputed student of this college made influence in Bangladesh's socio-political circumstances.\n\n==Faculties and departments==\nSaadat college comprises following four faculties:\n;Faculty of Arts ([[Bachelor degree|B.A]])\n* Department of [[English language|English]]\n* Department of [[Bengali language|Bengali]]\n* Department of [[History]]\n* Department of [[Philosophy]]\n* Department of [[Islamic history]] and [[Islamic culture|culture]]\n* Department of [[Islamic studies|Islamic study]]\n;Faculty of Science ([[Bachelor degree|B.SC]])\n* Department of [[Physics]]\n* Department of [[Chemistry]]\n* Department of [[Math]]\n* Department of [[Zoology]]\n* Department of [[Botany]]\n;Faculty of Social Science ([[Bachelor degree|B.S.S]])\n* Department of [[Economics]]\n* Department of [[Social welfare]]\n* Department of [[Political science]]\n;Faculty of Commerce ([[Bachelor degree|B.B.A.]])\n* Department of [[Accounting]]\n* Department of [[Management]]\n* Department of [[Marketing]]\n* Department of [[Banking]]  & [[Finance]]\n\nThe college offers [[Master degree]] in English, Zoology, Chemistry, Mathematicsa\n\n==Facilities==\n[[Image:GSC library.jpg|thumb|210px|left|Central Library]]\nThe main building of this college is surrounded within {{convert|27|acre|m2}} of area. Inside the campus area there are one college auditorium, two students common room, one central library, one sports office, one B.N.CC office room, one [[Rover Scout|Rover scouts]] office, one Mosque and one canteen available for students. There are 5 laboratories available for science faculty - (I) Physics (ii) Chemistry (iii) Math (iv) Zoology and (v) Botany. The college also has 16 seminar rooms.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\nThe college library has 200 rare medieval [[manuscripts]], including some other manuscripts written by [[Shahnama]].<ref name=\"GSC\"/> Since its inception, the college has been providing [[lodging|lodging facilities]] for its students.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}\n\n==Halls of residence==\n[[Image:Panni hall.jpg|thumb|210px|right|Wazed Ali Khan Panni Hall]]\n[[Image:Chhatrinibas.jpg|thumb|210px|right|Chhatrinibas Hall]]\nThere are 6 residential halls to provide housing for Saadat college students. 4 for males and 2 for females.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}} The halls for male students are:\n* Wazed Ali Khan Panni Hall\n* Ebrahim Khan Hall\n* Somman Hall\n* Uttara Hall\nAnd the halls for female students are:\n* Fazilatunnesa Hall\n* Chhatrinibas Hall\n\n==Alumni==\nThis is a partial list of notable alumni of Government Saadat College. Entries on this list should either have an accompanying existing article link which verifies they are an alumnus, or reliable sources as footnotes against the name.\n* [[Selim Al Din]] (dramatist)\n* [[Shajahan Siraj]] (ex-minister)\n* [[P. C. Sorcar]] (magician)\n* [[Bonde Ali Mia]] (poet)\n* [[Shamsul Haque]] (First Secretary of Awami Muslim League)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Karatia, Tangail]]\n\n==References==\n{{commons|Government Saadat College}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.facebook.com/saadatcollege Government Saadat College at Facebook]\n\n{{Public Colleges under National University in Bangladesh}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1926]]\n[[Category:1926 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Education in Tangail]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toShamsul Haque(link changed toShamsul Haque (Mymensingh politician)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_Saadat_College"}
{"title_page": "Jason Momoa", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor and model born in Hawaii}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jason Momoa\n| image              = Jason Momoa by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Momoa in 2018\n| birth_name         = Joseph Jason Namakaeha Momoa\n| height             =  \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1979|8|1}}\n| birth_place        = [[N\u0101n\u0101kuli, Hawaii|N\u0101n\u0101kuli]], [[Honolulu]], [[Hawaii]], U.S.\n| residence          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation         = {{Hlist|Actor|model}}\n| years_active       = 1999\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{Marriage|[[Lisa Bonet]]|2017}} \n| children           = 2 \n| relatives          = [[Zo\u00eb Kravitz]] (stepdaughter)\n| signature          = Jason Momoa autograph.png\n}}\n\n'''Joseph Jason Namakaeha Momoa'''<ref name=desmoinesregister /> (born August 1, 1979)<ref name=desmoinesregister /> is \nan American actor, best known for playing [[Khal Drogo]] in the [[HBO]] [[fantasy]] television series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'', [[Ronon Dex]] in ''[[Stargate Atlantis]], ''Declan Harp in the [[Canadian]] series ''[[Frontier (2016 TV series)|Frontier]]'', and [[Aquaman]] in the [[DC Extended Universe]] films ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'', ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]'', and ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nAn only child, Momoa was born in 1979 in [[N\u0101n\u0101kuli, Hawaii|N\u0101n\u0101kuli]], [[Honolulu]],\n[[Hawaii]] then as a teen his family moved to new zealand where he spent a few years ruining the vaginas at the local highschool, like absolutly wrecked them, some you can put an entire fist in,<ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\">{{cite news |url=https://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/12/16/hawaii-news/hawaii-born-actor-jason-momoas-role-in-aquaman-parallels-his-own-upbringing/ |title=Hawaii-born actor Jason Momoa's 'Aquaman' role parallels own upbringing |work=Star Advertiser |date=December 16, 2018 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> to Coni (Lemke), a photographer and Joseph Momoa, a painter.<ref name=desmoinesregister>{{cite news |first=Sophia |last=Ahmad |url=http://blogs.desmoinesregister.com/dmr/index.php/2010/02/19/interview-with-norwalk-conan-star-jason-momoa |title=Interview with Norwalk\u2019s \u2018Conan\u2019 star Jason Momoa |work=[[Des Moines Register]]|location=Iowa|date=February 19, 2010 |access-date=February 23, 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130408022415/http://blogs.desmoinesregister.com/dmr/index.php/2010/02/19/interview-with-norwalk-conan-star-jason-momoa |archive-date=April 8, 2013}}</ref> He was raised in [[Norwalk, Iowa]], by his mother.<ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\" /> His father is of [[Native Hawaiian]] ancestry<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.factinate.com/people/42-imposing-facts-jason-momoa/ |title=42 Imposing Facts About Jason Momoa |date=August 9, 2018 |first=Cadeem |last=Lalor |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.peoplesworld.org/article/aquaman-the-life-aquatic-with-hawaiian-polynesian-power-superhero-jason-momoa/ |title='Aquaman': The life aquatic with Hawaiian Polynesian Power superhero Jason Momoa |work=Peoples World |date=January 3, 2019 |first=Ed |last=Rampell |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> and his mother is of [[Germans|German]], [[Irish people|Irish]], and [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] descent.<ref name=\"Jason Momoa Interview\" /> After high school, Momoa attended college and initially majored in [[marine biology]] before switching to [[wildlife biology]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/redeye/ct-redeye-xpm-2014-03-04-47905420-story.html |title=Jason Momoa takes 'The Red Road' |first=Curt |last=Wagner |date=March 4, 2014 |work=The Chicago Tribune |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Jason momoa.jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Momoa during the filming of ''Stargate Atlantis'' in 2006]]\nIn 1998, Momoa was discovered by designer Eric Chandler and Takeo Kobayashi,<ref>{{cite web |title=Takeo Kobayashi |url=http://www.midweek.com/takeo-kobayashi/ |website=Midweek.com |date=December 19, 2012 |first=Chris |last=Fleck |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> who encouraged his [[Model (person)|modeling career]].  At 19 years old, he also worked part-time in a surf shop before being cast in the [[Action (genre)|action]] [[Dramatic programming|drama series]] ''[[Baywatch Hawaii]]'',<ref name=\"katiecouric1\">{{cite web |url=http://katiecouric.com/videos/game-of-thrones-jason-momoa/ |title=\"Game of Thrones\" Star Jason Momoa |publisher=KatieCouric.com |access-date=February 23, 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904033741/http://katiecouric.com/videos/game-of-thrones-jason-momoa/ |archive-date=September 4, 2014}}</ref> where he appeared as [[Jason Ioane]] (1999\u20132001).<ref>{{cite web |last=Kelly |first=Helen |url=https://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/667229/Game-of-Thrones-Jason-Momoa-Khal-Drogo-Baywatch-Hawaii-Model |title=Game of Thrones: Jason Momoa is unrecognisable as young model before Khal Drogo role |work=Daily Express |date=May 5, 2016 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to his appearances in ''[[North Shore (TV series)|North Shore]]'' (2004\u20132005), ''[[Johnson Family Vacation]]'' (2004), and ''[[Stargate: Atlantis]]'' (2005\u20132009), Momoa was cast as Roman in four episodes of the [[comedy-drama]] television series ''[[The Game (U.S. TV series)|The Game]]'' (2009). He portrayed the title protagonist in ''[[Conan the Barbarian (2011 film)|Conan the Barbarian]]'' (2011), a [[remake|reimagining]] of the 1982 film of the same name and a role made famous by [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]]. Momoa gained his role of [[Khal Drogo]] on HBO's ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' through his audition, in which he performed a [[Haka]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://time.com/4641078/game-of-thrones-jason-momoa-khal-drogo-audition/ |title=''Game of Thrones''<nowiki>'</nowiki> Jason Momoa Tells the Origin Story Behind His Viral Audition |website=Time.com |date=January 20, 2017 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> one of many intimidating [[M\u0101ori culture|M\u0101ori]] dances traditionally used to convey a challenge to an opponent, or a welcome to a visitor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maori.org.nz/waiata/default.php?pid=sp95&parent=85|title=Kapa Haka|last=|first=|date=1996|work=maori.org.nz/|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMomoa directed and co-wrote ''[[Road to Paloma]]'' (2014), an American [[drama]] [[thriller film]], together with writers Jonathan Hirschbein and Robert Homer Mollohan. The film stars Momoa, [[Sarah Shahi]], [[Lisa Bonet]], [[Michael Raymond-James]], and [[Wes Studi]].<ref name=\"collider\">{{cite web |title=Exclusive: Jason Momoa Talks CONAN; Reveals He's Writing and Directing ROAD TO PALOMA |url=http://collider.com/jason-momoa-conan-road-to-paloma-interview/ |publisher=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> It premiered at the [[Sarasota Film Festival|2014 Sarasota Film Festival]] in April 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/jason-momoas-road-to-paloma-to-premiere-in-2014-sarasota-film-festival-1201130089/ |title=Jason Momoa's 'Road to Paloma' to Premiere at Sarasota Film Festival |work=Variety |date=March 12, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> The film had a limited theatrical release on July 15, 2014 in [[New York City]] and [[Los Angeles]] and a VOD release.<ref>{{cite web |last=Schwartz |first=Terri |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/pop2it/2014/02/jason-momoa-landed-the-red-road-thanks-to-his-directorial-debut-road-to-paloma.html |title=Jason Momoa landed 'The Red Road' thanks to his directorial debut 'Road to Paloma' |work=Blog.zap2it.com |date=February 26, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302181100/http://blog.zap2it.com/pop2it/2014/02/jason-momoa-landed-the-red-road-thanks-to-his-directorial-debut-road-to-paloma.html |archive-date=March 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jason Momoa Supercon 2014.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Momoa in 2014]]\nIn March 2014, Momoa joined the dark comedy/thriller indie ''[[Sugar Mountain (film)|Sugar Mountain]]'' alongside [[Cary Elwes]] and [[Haley Webb]]; its principal photography was done in Alaska.<ref name=\"sugarmountain\">{{cite web |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/115943-cary-elwes-and-jason-momoa-to-climb-sugar-mountain |title=Cary Elwes and Jason Momoa to Climb Sugar Mountain |publisher=ComingSoon.net |date=March 12, 2014 |first=Silas |last=Lesnick |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cary-elwes-jason-momoa-join-indie-sugar-mountain-688082 |title=Cary Elwes, Jason Momoa Join Indie 'Sugar Mountain' |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=March 12, 2014 |first=Rebecca |last=Ford |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> He also starred as Phillip Kopus, a [[Ramapough Mountain Indians|Ramapough Mountain Indian]], on the [[SundanceTV]] drama series ''[[The Red Road (TV series)|The Red Road]]'' (2014\u20132015).<ref name=\"redroad\">{{cite web |url=http://seriable.com/the-red-road-cancelled-by-sundancetv-after-two-seasons/ |website=Seriable.com |title=The Red Road Cancelled By SundanceTV After Two Seasons |date=May 23, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826135115/http://seriable.com/the-red-road-cancelled-by-sundancetv-after-two-seasons/ |archive-date=August 26, 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, Momoa was reported to have been cast in the role of [[Aquaman]]. He first played the role in a cameo in the superhero film ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]'',<ref name=\"JasonMomoaAquaman\">{{cite news |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/aquaman-jason-momoa-batman-v-superman-dawn-of-justice/ |title=Jason Momoa Is Aquaman in 'Batman V Superman: Dawn Of Justice' |access-date=February 23, 2019 |newspaper=[[/Film]] |date=June 14, 2014 |first=Peter |last=Sciretta}}</ref><ref name=\"JasonMomoaAquaman2\">{{cite web |url=https://uproxx.com/hitfix/jason-momoa-will-play-aquaman-in-dawn-of-justice-and-we-know-how-it-will-happen/ |title=Jason Momoa Will Play Aquaman in 'Dawn of Justice', and We Know how It Will Happen |last=McWeeny |first=Drew |work=Hitfix |date=June 14, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"JasonMomoaAquaman3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jason-momoa-playing-aquaman-batman-711899 |title=Jason Momoa to Play Aquaman in 'Batman v. Superman: Dawn of Justice' |first1=Rebecca |last1=Ford |first2=Borys |last2=Kit |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=June 16, 2014 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> marking Aquaman's live action theatrical debut. Momoa played the character in a leading role in the 2017 [[ensemble film]] ''[[Justice League (film)|Justice League]]''. He then starred in the ''[[Aquaman (film)|Aquaman]]'' solo film, which released in late 2018.<ref name=\"aquabat\">{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/aquaman-movie-actor-jason-momoa-official/ |title=It's Official: Jason Momoa is 'Aquaman'; Solo Movie Coming 2018 |date=October 15, 2014 |work=Screen Rant |access-date=February 23, 2019 |first=Andrew |last=Dice}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/dc-movie-slate-revealed/ |title=DC Comics Movies Announced: 'Suicide Squad,' 'Wonder Woman,' 'Justice League,' 'The Flash,' 'Aquaman' |work=Slashfilm |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"V-Aquaman\">{{cite web |first=Justin |last=Kroll |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/aquaman-james-wan-directing-1201511748/ |title=James Wan to Direct 'Aquaman' for Warner Bros. |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=June 3, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> He also reprised this role in ''[[The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.avclub.com/jason-momoas-aquaman-will-splash-around-in-the-lego-mov-1831379994 |title=Jason Momoa's Aquaman will splash around in ''The Lego Movie 2'' |first=William |last=Hughes |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Momoa portrayed Connor in the Canadian horror action film ''[[Wolves (2014 film)|Wolves]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/91414/uk-exclusive-wolves-gag-reel-serves-howlers/ |title=UK Exclusive: Wolves Gag Reel Serves Up a Few Howlers |first=Gareth |last=Jones |date=February 28, 2015 |work=DreadCentral.com |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> and starred in the Sci-fi horror movie ''[[Debug (film)|Debug]];'' it was written and directed by Momoa's former ''Stargate Atlantis'' co-star, British-born Canadian actor [[David Hewlett]]. In February 2015, it was announced that he would portray a [[Cannibalism|cannibal]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/89009/jason-momoa-eats-bad-batch-human-flesh/ |title=Jason Momoa Eats a Bad Batch of Human Flesh |first=Steve |last=Barton |website=DreadCentral.com |date=February 6, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> in the drama thriller film ''The Bad Batch''.<ref name=\"thebadbatch\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/jason-momoa-in-talks-to-star-in-cannibal-love-story-the-bad-batch-for-annapurna-vice-exclusive/ |title=Jason Momoa in Talks to Star in Cannibal Love Story 'The Bad Batch' for Annapurna, Vice (Exclusive) |first=Jeff |last=Sneider |date=February 6, 2015 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> In 2015, Momoa was cast in the Canadian action film ''[[Braven]]'', which was released on February 2, 2018.\n\nIn early 2017, he signed onto the official ''Just Cause'' movie series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/jason-momoa-just-cause-movie-1202003798/ |title='Aquaman's' Jason Momoa to Star in 'Just Cause' Film Adaptation |first=Dave |last=McNary |date=March 7, 2017 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/entertainment/2017/03/jason-momoa-lands-just-cause-movie-lead.html |title=Jason Momoa lands Just Cause movie lead |date=August 3, 2017 |website=newshub.co.nz |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2018, Momoa was cast for Apple's upcoming future-based drama series [[See (TV series)|''See'']].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jason-momoa-star-apple-drama-see-1126050 |title=Jason Momoa to Star in Apple Drama 'See' |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=July 10, 2018 |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/jason-momoa-apple-see-1202869906/ |title=Jason Momoa to Star in Apple Sci-Fi Series 'See' |last=Otterson |first=Joe |date=July 10, 2018 |work=Variety |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2019, Momoa was cast as [[Duncan Idaho]] in the upcoming [[Denis Villeneuve]] film ''[[Dune (2020 film)|Dune]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/jason-momoa-dune-aquaman-frank-herbert-denis-villenueve-1202557876/ |title='Aquaman's Jason Momoa Joins Killer Cast Of Denis Villenueve's 'Dune' |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |date=February 14, 2019 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/uncategorized/jason-momoa-dune-reboot-legendary-1203140272/ |title=Jason Momoa Joins Timothee Chalamet, Javier Bardem in 'Dune' Reboot |first=Justin |last=Kroll |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=February 14, 2019 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, Momoa appeared in a half time commercial for Rocket Mortgage for Superbowl 54. He also appeared in the teaser for \"Scary Little Green Men\" by [[Ozzy Osbourne]] from his album [[Ordinary Man (Ozzy Osbourne album)|Ordinary Man]].\n\n==Personal life==\n[[File:Jason Momoa by Gage Skidmore.jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Momoa in July 2017]]\nMomoa began a relationship with actress [[Lisa Bonet]] in 2005.<ref name=\"horse\">{{cite news |url=https://abc7.com/archive/8318234/ |title=Jason Momoa of 'Conan the Barbarian' talks about his horse fears |date=August 20, 2011 |first=Olivia |last=Allin |work=OnTheRedCarpet.com |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> Although it was previously believed that Momoa and Bonet married on November 15, 2007, the couple did not legally marry until October 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/jason-momoa-lisa-bonet-officially-marry-in-secret-wedding/ |title=Jason Momoa and Lisa Bonet Just Got Officially Married: Details on Their Secret Wedding |date=November 2, 2017 |work=Us Weekly |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> Through his marriage to Bonet, Momoa is the stepfather to [[Zo\u00eb Kravitz]]. In July 2007, Bonet gave birth to their first child, a daughter.<ref name=\"horse\"/> Their second child, a son, was born in December 2008.<ref>{{cite web |date=January 9, 2009 |url=https://www.today.com/popculture/lisa-bonets-new-babys-name-mouthful-wbna28584888 |title=Lisa Bonet's New Baby's Name Is a Mouthful |work=[[Access Hollywood]] |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMomoa learned martial arts for his role as Ronon in ''Stargate Atlantis''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stargate.mgm.com/view/content/1418/ |title=Jason Momoa on Martial Arts |date=August 14, 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304051021/http://stargate.mgm.com/view/content/1418/ |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> and for ''Conan''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.starpulse.com/Actors/Momoa,_Jason/Biography/ |title=Jason Momoa Biography |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304043004/http://www.starpulse.com/Actors/Momoa,_Jason/Biography/ |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> In 2017, Momoa started practicing [[Brazilian jiu-jitsu]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Jason Momoa Trains Jiu-Jitsu |url=https://www.bjjee.com/articles/jason-momoa-trains-jiu-jitsu/ |website=BJJEE |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Jason Momoa's Instagram post |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BQhSoriBswN/ |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> Momoa has also practiced proper screaming technique with Oli Peters, the vocalist of [[technical death metal]] band [[Archspire]] for a war cry scene in ''[[See (TV series)|See]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.revolvermag.com/culture/jason-momoa-trained-archspire-vocalist-learn-war-cry-see/|title=Jason Momoa Trained with Archspire Vocalist to Learn War Cry for 'See'|date=November 19, 2019|website=Revolver}}</ref>\n\nHe has multiple tattoos. The most notable tattoo is a halfsleeve on his left forearm, which is a tribute to his family god, or \u201c[[aumakua]]\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a22515826/jason-momoa-aquaman-tattoos/|title=Are Jason Momoa's 'Aquaman' Tattoos Actually Real?|last=Friedman|first=Megan|date=2018-07-23|website=Men's Health|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-24}}</ref> He is a fan of [[heavy metal music]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2019/06/13/actor-jason-momoa-hung-out-with-slayer-and-anthrax/|title=Actor Jason Momoa Hung Out with Slayer and Anthrax|date=June 13, 2019|website=MetalSucks}}</ref> and has noted that he \"build[s] [his] characters off of metal songs\";<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2018/12/11/jason-momoa-drew-inspiration-for-playing-aquaman-from-metallica-black-sabbath-and-tool/|title=Jason Momoa Drew Inspiration for Playing Aquaman from Metallica, Black Sabbath, and Tool &#124; MetalSucks|date=December 11, 2018|via=www.metalsucks.net}}</ref> he has invited members of [[Archspire]] to appear in cameos in the first episode of ''[[See (TV series)|See]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metalsucks.net/2019/11/02/jason-momoa-recruits-archspire-members-for-new-apple-tv-show/|title=Jason Momoa Recruits Archspire Members for New Apple TV+ Show &#124; MetalSucks|date=November 2, 2019|via=www.metalsucks.net}}</ref>\n\nMomoa is noted for having a close friendship with [[Emilia Clarke]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/emilia-clarkes-birthday-post-for-jason-momoa-will-make-you-cherish-their-friendship-more-18367274|title=Emilia Clark's Birthday Post For Jason Momoa Will Make You Cherish Their Friendship More|website=Elite Daily|language=en|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=October 29|first=Julie Scagell|title=Jason Momoa And Emilia Clarke's Genuine Friendship Is The Content We Need RN|date=2019-10-29|url=https://www.scarymommy.com/jason-momoa-emilia-clarke-graham-norton-show/|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20|last2=2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thethings.com/15-sweet-things-to-know-about-jason-momoa-and-emilia-clarkes-friendship/|title=15 Sweet Things To Know About Jason Momoa And Emilia Clarke's Friendship|date=2020-02-11|website=TheThings|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n===Facial scar===\nOn November 15, 2008, Momoa was slashed in the face with a broken beer glass by a man during an altercation at the Birds Cafe, a tavern in [[Hollywood, California]].<ref name=\"NBC1\">{{cite web |title=Man Pleads Not Guilty To Assaulting \"Stargate Atlantis\" Actor |url=https://www.nbclosangeles.com/entertainment/celebrity/Man-Pleads-Not-Guilty-to-Assaulting-Stargate-Atlantis-Actor.html |publisher=[[KNBC]] |date=July 17, 2009 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"latimes\">{{cite web |url=https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2009/10/5year-sentence-for-man-who-attacked-stargate-atalantis-actor-who-required-140-stitches.html |title=Five-year sentence for man who attacked 'Stargate Atlantis' actor Jason Momoa |last=Winton |first=Richard |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=October 7, 2009 |access-date=February 23, 2019}}</ref> He received approximately 140&nbsp;stitches during [[reconstructive surgery]] and the scar is apparent in his later work.<ref name=\"NBC1\"/> The assailant was sentenced to five years in prison for the attack.<ref name=\"latimes\"/>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n<!--TV movies go in with the 'Television' section as per WP:FILMOGRAPHY \u2013 do NOT add here -->\n<!--Organize table in terms of domestic and/or international theatrical/VOD release date; festival premiere is not a release date -->\n<!-- Please note: do NOT use \"rowspans\" per WP:FILMOGRAPHY -->\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Role\n!scope=\"col\"| Director\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Johnson Family Vacation]]''\n| 2004\n| Navarro\n| {{sort|Erskin|[[Christopher Erskin]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Pipeline (film)|Pipeline]]''\n| 2007\n| Kai\n| {{sort|Alan|Jordan Alan}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Conan the Barbarian (2011 film)|Conan the Barbarian]]''\n| 2011\n| [[Conan the Barbarian|Conan]]\n| {{sort|Nispel|[[Marcus Nispel]]}}\n| [[National Association of Theatre Owners|CinemaCon Award for Male Rising Star]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Bullet to the Head]]''\n| 2012\n| Keegan\n| {{sort|Hill|[[Walter Hill (director)|Walter Hill]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Road to Paloma]]''\n| rowspan=3|2014\n| {{sort|Wolf|Robert Wolf}}\n| Himself\n| Also director, producer and co-writer\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"collider\" />\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Debug (film)|Debug]]''\n| Iam\n| {{sort|Hewlett|[[David Hewlett]]}}\n|\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n!scope=row| ''[[Wolves (2014 film)|Wolves]]''\n| Connor\n| {{sort|Hayter|[[David Hayter]]}}\n| \n|